==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrymouth
<hw>Wry"mouth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of large, elongated, marine fishes of
the genus <gen>Cryptacanthodes</gen>, especially <spn>Cryptacanthodes
maculatus</spn> of the American coast. A whitish variety is called
<stype>ghostfish</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wryneck</ent>⟦br⟧
